text.section:
The cabinet shall:
Fix and announce dates for the examinations;
Prepare and make available forms for application for a water well driller certificate;
See that all examinations for certificates are graded;
Prepare and issue certificates to those entitled thereto;
Upon recommendation of the board, promulgate rules and regulations as are necessary to carry out the purposes of KRS 223.405 to 223.460, including the conducting of examinations and the suspension and revocation of certificates;
Inspect and investigate water wells to ensure compliance with the provisions of KRS 223.405 to 223.460;
Maintain and publish annually a register showing the names and addresses of certified water well drillers and distribute a copy of same to each certified individual free of charge;
Maintain under the control of the executive secretary and treasurer a record showing:
The names and addresses of all certified individuals under KRS 223.425;
The dates of issuance and renewal of all certificates;
The date and substance of the charges set forth in any complaint for suspension or revocation of any certificate;
The date and substance of all petitions for reinstatement of certificates; and
The final order on such complaints and petitions.
